trans-unit.source: Remote Python Development in Visual Studio Code
trans-unit.target: Remote Python Development in Visual Studio Code

trans-unit.source: Dan Taylor | May 2nd, 2019
trans-unit.target: Dan Taylor | May 2nd, 2019

trans-unit.source: Today at PyCon 2019, Microsoft’s Python and Visual Studio Code team announced remote development in Visual Studio Code, enabling Visual Studio Code developers to work in development setups where their code and tools are running remotely inside of docker containers, remote SSH hosts, and Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL), while you still get a rich and seamless user experience locally.
trans-unit.target: Today at PyCon 2019, Microsoft’s Python and Visual Studio Code team announced remote development in Visual Studio Code, enabling Visual Studio Code developers to work in development setups where their code and tools are running remotely inside of docker containers, remote SSH hosts, and Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL), while you still get a rich and seamless user experience locally.

trans-unit.source: Python in Visual Studio Code – April 2019 Release
trans-unit.target: Python in Visual Studio Code – April 2019 Release

trans-unit.source: Luciana de Melo e Abud | April 23rd, 2019
trans-unit.target: Luciana de Melo e Abud | April 23rd, 2019

trans-unit.source: We are pleased to announce that the April 2019 release of the Python Extension for Visual Studio Code is now available.
trans-unit.target: We are pleased to announce that the April 2019 release of the Python Extension for Visual Studio Code is now available.

trans-unit.source: You can download the Python extension from the Marketplace, or install it directly from the extension gallery in Visual Studio Code.
trans-unit.target: You can download the Python extension from the Marketplace, or install it directly from the extension gallery in Visual Studio Code.

trans-unit.source: You can learn more about Python support in Visual Studio Code in the documentation.
trans-unit.target: You can learn more about Python support in Visual Studio Code in the documentation.

trans-unit.source: Data Science with Python in Visual Studio Code
trans-unit.target: Data Science with Python in Visual Studio Code

trans-unit.source: Rong Lu | November 8th, 2018
trans-unit.target: Rong Lu | November 8th, 2018

trans-unit.source: Today we’re very excited to announce the availability of Data Science features in the Python extension for Visual Studio Code!
trans-unit.target: Today we’re very excited to announce the availability of Data Science features in the Python extension for Visual Studio Code!

trans-unit.source: With the addition of these features, you can now work with data interactively in Visual Studio Code, whether it is for exploring data or for incorporating machine learning models into applications, making Visual Studio Code an exciting new option for those who prefer an editor for data science tasks.
trans-unit.target: With the addition of these features, you can now work with data interactively in Visual Studio Code, whether it is for exploring data or for incorporating machine learning models into applications, making Visual Studio Code an exciting new option for those who prefer an editor for data science tasks.
